### What problem does this feature solve?
I'm writing a Web Component that will be included in pages that may have their own copy of Vue loaded.
This causes errors (at least in dev mode) like "$attrs is readonly" - I'm not sure what the effect of these errors is.

The problem is caused by the following code at the end of src/index.js

```
if (inBrowser && window.Vue) {
  window.Vue.use(VueRouter)
}
```

### What does the proposed API look like?
I'm not sure what the best way to fix this would be - perhaps provide a separate .js file that doesn't have the auto registration?
```
import Vue from 'vue';
import VueRouter from 'vue-router/no-auto-registration';

Vue.use(VueRouter);
```

